cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.THEORY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper defines a logic for expressing properties of higher-order programs with algebraic effects. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with program equivalence and algebraic effects in the context of programming languages. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with the study of program equivalence, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the formal study of program equivalence and algebraic effects. 
- cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper deals with the theoretical aspects of program equivalence and algebraic effects.
